Html:
I would like to request the possibility to convert a cell range in a table, allowing to &quot;attach&quot; a &quot;total row&quot; on the bottom, and to dinamically sort fields on the header.<br />
<br />
Something like:<br />
<pre><code>// Convert a specifc cell range to a table
$PHPExcel-&gt;getActiveSheet()-&gt;formatRangeAsTable(&quot;A1:F88&quot;, &quot;table1&quot;); 
// AND / OR
// Convert the entire cell range to a table   
$PHPExcel-&gt;getActiveSheet()-&gt;convertToTable(&quot;table1&quot;);

// May throw exception if &quot;table1&quot; already exists.</code></pre>

Possible actions for tables:<br />
<pre><code>// Tables have unique names and can be referenced accross sheets, and can be selected without knowing the sheet name
$table = $PHPExcel-&gt;getTable(&quot;table1&quot;); 
$table-&gt;setTotalsRow(true) # Add a total row
      -&gt;setHeader(true); # Tells that the table include headers, allowing dynamic sorting

$table-&gt;addColumn(...) # Add a column to the entire table range
      -&gt;addRow(...) # Add a new row to the table</code></pre>

May allow associative data:<br />
<pre><code>$table = $PHPExcel-&gt;getTable(&quot;table1&quot;); 
$table-&gt;setHeaderKeys(array('date', 'client', 'qty', 'sale_total'));

foreach ($table-&gt;getRows() as $row) {
    // Magic function allow the use of header keys to get/set data
    $row-&gt;setDate($today);
}</code></pre>
